Name: TM01

Name: TM02

Name: TM15

Name: TM16
Description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to suppress damage from special attacks for five turns.

Name: TM17

Name: TM18

Name: TM20

Name: TM22

Name: TM23

Name: TM24

Name: TM25

Name: TM26

Name: TM27
Description: A full-power attack that grows more powerful the more the user likes its Trainer.

Name: TM28

Name: TM29

Name: TM33
Description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to suppress damage from physical attacks for five turns.

Name: TM36

Name: TM89
Description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

Name: Lunalium-Z

Name: Rift Seed

Name: Reforged Key
Description: A key to the strange house south of Sashila Village. It's brand new!

Name: Lake Postcard
Description: A postcard with a lovely picture of Gregorian Lake on it.

Name: Skuntank Crest

Name: Zone Zero Key
Description: A key to open the gate to Zone Zero from Alamissa Urben.

Name: Whiscash Crest

Name: Enigmatic Key

Name: Infernape Crest

Name: Empoleon Crest

Name: Magic Wand
Description: A stick Braixen used to use for her attacks.

Name: Dark Matter Core
Description: A core filled to the brim with Dark Matter.

Name: RM01
Description: The user sharpens its claws to boost its Attack stat and accuracy.

Name: RM02
Description: This move deals double damage if the user is hurt by the target that turn.

Name: RM03
Description: The user fires an electric blast like a cannon to inflict damage and cause paralysis.

Name: RM04
Description: The user waggles a finger and stimulates its brain into randomly using nearly any move.

Name: RM05

Name: RM06

Name: RM07

Name: RM08

Name: Castform Crest

Name: RM09
Description: The user strikes with a simultaneous three-beam attack. May also burn or freeze or paralyze the target.

Name: Sweet Apple

Name: Cracked Pot
Description: A peculiar teapot that can make a certain species of Pokémon evolve. It may be cracked, but tea poured from it is delicious.

Name: Rusted Shield
Description: It is said that a hero used this shield to halt a terrible disaster in ancient times. It's grown rusty and worn.

Name: Fossilized Drake

Name: Fossilized Fish
Description: The fossil of an ancient Pokémon that once lived in the sea. What it looked like is a mystery.

Name: TM157

Description: Candy that was made by The Puppet Master. It will level up your Pokemon an average amount.

Name: Mysterious Black Box
Description: A mysterious black box. It does nothing.

Name: Speed Card
Description: A card that allows the owner to participate in the Speed EV center service.

Description: Gains Fighting-type STAB and resistances. Slicing moves always result in critical hit.

Name: Sky Relic

Name: Xen Waste

Name: Nightmare Fuel
Description: Excess waste from the Ligosomnia Engine. It seems to cause Pokemon to mutate...

Name: Interceptor's Wish
Description: An item that allows the Interceptor to scatter their strength to aid others.

Name: Interceptium-Z (old)

Name: Galarica Wreath

Name: Blue Orb
Description: A shiny blue orb that is said to have a legend tied to it. It's known to have a deep connection with the Hoenn Region.

Name: Reset Disc- ATK

Name: Reset Disc- DEF

Name: Peat Block

Name: Black Augurite

Name: Puppet Doubloon
Description: A coin with the Puppet Master's true face on it. Its use is unknown.

Name: Stabilizer

Name: Robo Ren's Cloak
Description: A piece of Robo Ren's Sashilan Cloak.

Name: Pearl Core
Description: Spacea's Orb. Only a memory now.

Name: Diamond Core
Description: Tiempa's Diamond. Only a memory now.

Name: Red Gem

Name: H-Disk

Name: Unown Crest
Description: Filler text.

Description: A memory disc that contains ???-type data. It changes the type of the holder if held by a certain Pokémon.

Name: Golden Lantern
Description: A golden item that allows for the use of Flash without the use of TMs.

Name: Remote PC
Description: Allows remote connection to the storage system. Requires and consumes one Cell Battery per use.

Name: Pink Petal
Description: A petal cultivated from GDC's Botanical Garden. It changes the form of certain species of Pokémon.

Name: Green Petal
Description: A petal cultivated from GDC's Botanical Garden. It changes the form of certain species of Pokémon.

Name: Orange Petal
Description: A petal cultivated from GDC's Botanical Garden. It changes the form of certain species of Pokémon.

Name: Blue Petal
Description: A petal cultivated from GDC's Botanical Garden. It changes the form of certain species of Pokémon.

Name: Mirror Lure
Description: An item to be held. One polarity draws in identical species to the holder, while the other allows for quick escape.

Name: Puzzle Box
Description: A dusty puzzle box found in Flora's room. It seems to have been manufactured by the Weather Institute.

Name: Pumpkin
Description: A nicely sized pumpkin wrassled from an angry Gourgeist.

Name: Talon's Glove
Description: Talon's Glove. A symbol of his insecurity. Only a memory now.

Name: Florin's ID
Description: Florin's Gov. ID. Only a memory now.

Name: Furret Crest
Description: Upon switching in, Furret loses 25% of its Max HP to create a substitute.

Name: HM01
Description: The target is cut with a scythe or claw. It can also be used to cut down thin trees.

Name: HM02
Description: The user soars, then strikes on the second turn. It can also be used to fly to any familiar town.

Name: HM03
Description: It swamps the area around the user with a giant wave. It can also be used for crossing water.

Name: HM04
Description: The target is slugged with a punch thrown at maximum power. This move can also be used to move boulders.

Name: HM05
Description: The user charges the target at an awesome speed. It can also be used to climb a waterfall.

Name: HM06
Description: Diving on the first turn, the user floats up and attacks on the second. It can be used for diving in the ocean.
